      boolean enoughFuel()
      This method simply returns a boolean indicating the state of the fuel tank inside a Car the state of the fuel tank is either there is an enough amount of fuel inside to apply the move in this case it returns true or the amount is not sufficient then it returns false.

    • Method Detail

      • enoughFuel

        public boolean enoughFuel()

        This method simply returns a boolean indicating the state of the fuel tank inside a Car the state of the fuel tank is either there is an enough amount of fuel inside to apply the move in this case it returns true or the amount is not sufficient then it returns false. This method is an override method to the method in the parent class Vehicle, in order to make the judgement of fuel sufficiency suitable for vehicles of type Car.

        Overrides:
        enoughFuel in class Vehicle
        See Also:
        Vehicle.enoughFuel(), returns boolean True if the fuel is enough, false if not
